-- Baltika, Estonian Clothier, Says Sales Rose 7% in January
-- B y   O t t   U m m e l a s
-- 2012-02-01T13:34:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-01/baltika-estonian-clothier-says-sales-rose-7-in-january.html
Baltika AS (BLT1T) , the third-biggest Baltic
clothing maker, said total sales for January increased 7 percent
from a year earlier, according to a regulatory statement in
Tallinn.  Retail revenue rose 16 percent in the three Baltic
countries, while sales in  Russia  rose 2 percent and retail
revenue in Ukraine declined 1 percent, Baltika said today. The
company closed four stores in Russia during the month.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ott Ummelas in Tallinn at 
 oummelas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
